isky elsewhere."},{"label":"Earnings momentum","value":9.47,"unit":"% YoY","status":"ok","read":"Profit up 9% YoY \u2014 modest.","meaning":"Trailing-twelve-month net profit vs the year-ago TTM (and whether the YoY rate is rising = 'accelerating').","why_useful":"Improving, accelerating earnings tend to drive re-rating; falling profit warns of a deteriorating business.","why_it_can_fail":"TTM can be lumpy for cyclicals/one-offs; cross-check the multi-year trend on the Fundamentals tab."}]},"valuation":{"ok":true,"is_bank":false,"pe_now":154.9,"pe_percentile":43.0,"median_pe":162.8,"earnings_yield_pct":0.65,"pb":4.26,"ev_ebitda":45.42,"quality_score":60.0,"pat_cagr_5y_pct":null,"peg":null,"cheapness":{"status":"ok","read":"P/E at the 43-percentile of its 10-yr range \u2014 mid-range vs its own history."},"expectations":"Trades at 154.9\u00d7 earnings; multi-year growth not estimable, so 'priced-in' growth is unclear.","cyclical_caveat":null,"meaning":"P/E percentile = where today's price-to-earnings sits within the stock's own last-10-yr range (low = cheap vs its past). Paired with the Quality score and 5-yr profit growth so a cheap multiple is judged against business strength, not in isolation.","why_useful":"Cheapness only matters relative to quality and growth \u2014 a low P/E on a declining or peak-cyclical business is a trap, not a bargain.","why_it_can_fail":"P/E breaks for loss-makers / one-offs; for banks use P/B not EV/EBITDA; a multiple cheap vs history can stay cheap if the business has structurally de-rated."},"ownership":{"ok":true,"na":null,"holders":{"Promoter":{"periods":["Dec 2024","Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[89.01,89.01,89.01,89.01,89.01,89.01],"latest_pct":89.01,"chg_1y_pp":0.0},"FII":{"periods":["Dec 2024","Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[2.18,1.98,1.85,1.79,1.61,1.61],"latest_pct":1.61,"chg_1y_pp":-0.37},"DII":{"periods":["Dec 2024","Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025",